      • addToStores

        protected static java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object>> addToStores(Data data,
                                                                                                                      java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object>> stores,
                                                                                                                      int totalAmount,
                                                                                                                      java.lang.String vaccineID,
                                                                                                                      java.lang.String creationDate,
                                                                                                                      java.lang.String expirationDate)
        Adds the given amount of vaccines with the given vaccineID and expirationDate to the given stores. Currently, adds vaccines to the first store with the available capacity, future versions should be more selective in which store to put it in (e.g. one which will give it the best shelf life)
        Parameters:
        data - Used to get the current date and the vaccine hash map from the vaccineID
        stores - the stores to add vaccines to, in the format in the format HashMap>
        totalAmount - the amount of vaccines to add
        vaccineID - the type of vaccine to be stored
        creationDate - the date the vaccines were created (assumed to be the current date if not given)
        expirationDate - the date the vaccines will expire
        Returns:
        the modified stores hashmap, in the format HashMap>
